  "prompt": "Can I get infected with an STD from getting oral sex without protection?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be at risk of contracting sexually transmitted diseases (STDs) from receiving oral sex without protection. While the risk is generally lower compared to vaginal or anal sex, several STDs can still be transmitted through oral sex. These include, but are not limited to:\n\n- Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV)\n- Gonorrhea\n- Chlamydia\n- Syphilis\n- Herpes (HSV-1 and HSV-2)\n- Human Papillomavirus (HPV)\n\nUsing protection, such as condoms or dental dams, can significantly reduce the risk of transmitting or contracting STDs during oral sex. Regular testing and open communication with sexual partners about sexual health can also help manage and reduce risks. If you have concerns about potential exposure to STDs, it's a good idea to consult a healthcare professional for advice and testing.",
